NAME
       Utils - Utility commands in Tix 3.6.

SYNOPSIS
       tixDescendants pathName

       tixDisableAll pathName

       tixEnableAll pathName

       tixListGetSingle pathName

       tixSetEntry pathName string

       tixStdDlgBtns pathName ?options?


DESCRIPTION
       tixDescendants  returns  a list of all the descendant wid-
       gets of pathName plus pathName itself.

       tixDisableAll disables pathName and all its descendants.

       tixEnableAll enables pathName and all its descendants.

       tixListGetSingle returns the  first  selected  item  in  a
       listbox  widget.  If no items are selected, it returns the
       empty string.

       tixSetEntry sets the string inside the entry widget  path-
       Name.

       tixStdDlgBtns creates a DlgBtns widget with the name path-
       Name. Additional options are also used  to  configure  the
       DlgBtns widget. It contains four standard buttons

       in  turn  be  configured using the normal subwidget access
       mechanism.


AUTHOR
       Ioi Kim Lam - ioi@graphics.cis.upenn.edu


KEYWORDS
       TIX, DlgBtns, Container Widgets.
